# Firmware Versioning

## Two independent version lines

| Target | Hardware | Version line | App display format |
|--------|----------|-------------|-------------------|
| USB | WiCAN USB-C3 (ESP32-C3) | `v1.5.x` | `openRS_ USB v1.5-rc.5` |
| PRO | WiCAN Pro (ESP32-S3) | `v1.0.x` | `openRS_ PRO v1.0` |

USB and PRO are **separate products** with independent version numbers. They share the same `focusrs` component source but have different upstream bases, SoCs, and release cadences.

## Version string locations

Two places define the version string. **Both must match** for each target:

1. **`firmware/components/focusrs/focusrs.h`** — `OPENRS_FW_VERSION` (compile-time, used in ESP log output)
2. **`firmware/patches/apply_patches.py`** — `OPENRS_FW_VERSION` (injected into SLCAN/WebSocket probe response)

Both files use a dict keyed by target name (`"usb"` / `"pro"`).

## How the app displays it

The firmware responds to `OPENRS?` with `OPENRS:<version>`. The Android app prepends `"openRS_ "`:
- USB firmware `"USB v1.5-rc.5"` shows as **"openRS_ USB v1.5-rc.5"**
- PRO firmware `"PRO v1.0"` shows as **"openRS_ PRO v1.0"**

The `USB` or `PRO` prefix is part of the version string so users can identify which hardware variant they're running.

## When bumping versions

- Bump USB and PRO independently. A USB release does not require a PRO release.
- Update both `focusrs.h` and `apply_patches.py` version dicts.
- Clear the build cache (`rm -rf firmware/.build/<target>`) if only `apply_patches.py` changed, since patched sources are cached.
- RC suffixes: `PRO v1.0-rc.2`, `USB v1.5-rc.6`. Stable releases drop the suffix: `PRO v1.0`, `USB v1.5`.

## GitHub release tags

- USB: `fw-usb-v1.5-rc.5` (pre-release) or `fw-usb-v1.5` (stable)
- PRO: `fw-pro-v1.0-rc.1` (pre-release) or `fw-pro-v1.0` (stable)
